HEADWORD: Frondescence
<hw>Fron*des"cence</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>The time at which each species of plants unfolds its
leaves.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The act of bursting into leaf.</def>
<rj><au>Milne. Martyn.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

